events.description: Henry V is crowned Holy Roman Emperor.
events.html: • 1111 – Henry V is crowned Holy Roman Emperor.[1]

events.description: Constantinople falls to the Crusaders of the Fourth Crusade, temporarily ending the Byzantine Empire.
events.html: • 1204 – Constantinople falls to the Crusaders of the Fourth Crusade, temporarily ending the Byzantine Empire.[2]

events.description: Thirteen Years' War: the beginning of the Battle for Kneiphof.
events.html: • 1455 – Thirteen Years' War: the beginning of the Battle for Kneiphof.[3]

events.description: Samurai Miyamoto Musashi defeats Sasaki Kojirō in a duel at Funajima island.
events.html: • 1612 – Samurai Miyamoto Musashi defeats Sasaki Kojirō in a duel at Funajima island.[4]

events.description: Samuel Argall, having captured Pocahontas in Passapatanzy, Virginia, sets off with her to Jamestown with the intention of exchanging her for English prisoners held by her father.
events.html: • 1613 – Samuel Argall, having captured Pocahontas in Passapatanzy, Virginia, sets off with her to Jamestown with the intention of exchanging her for English prisoners held by her father.[5]

events.description: The Sikh religion is formalised as the Khalsa
events.html: • 1699 – The Sikh religion is formalised as the Khalsa – the brotherhood of Warrior-Saints – by Guru Gobind Singh in northern India, in accordance with the Nanakshahi calendar.[6]

events.description: George Frideric Handel's oratorio Messiah makes its world premiere in Dublin, Ireland.
events.html: • 1742 – George Frideric Handel's oratorio Messiah makes its world premiere in Dublin, Ireland.[7]

events.description: American Revolutionary War: American forces are ambushed and defeated in the Battle of Bound Brook, New Jersey.
events.html: • 1777 – American Revolutionary War: American forces are ambushed and defeated in the Battle of Bound Brook, New Jersey.[8]

events.description: The Roman Catholic Relief Act 1829 gives Roman Catholics in the United Kingdom the right to vote and to sit in Parliament.
events.html: • 1829 – The Roman Catholic Relief Act 1829 gives Roman Catholics in the United Kingdom the right to vote and to sit in Parliament.[9]

entities.name: Roman Catholicism in the United Kingdom

events.description: Lajos Kossuth presents the Hungarian Declaration of Independence in a closed session of the National Assembly.
events.html: • 1849 – Lajos Kossuth presents the Hungarian Declaration of Independence in a closed session of the National Assembly.[10]

events.description: American Civil War: Union forces surrender Fort Sumter to Confederate forces.
events.html: • 1861 – American Civil War: Union forces surrender Fort Sumter to Confederate forces.[11]

events.description: American Civil War: Raleigh, North Carolina is occupied by Union forces.
events.html: • 1865 – American Civil War: Raleigh, North Carolina is occupied by Union forces.[12]

events.description: The New York City Metropolitan Museum of Art is founded.
events.html: • 1870 – The New York City Metropolitan Museum of Art is founded.[13]

events.description: The Colfax massacre: More than 60 to 150 black men are murdered in Colfax, Louisiana, while surrendering to a mob of former Confederate soldiers and members of the Ku Klux Klan.
events.html: • 1873 – The Colfax massacre: More than 60 to 150 black men are murdered in Colfax, Louisiana, while surrendering to a mob of former Confederate soldiers and members of the Ku Klux Klan.[14]

events.description: The 31 March Incident leads to the overthrow of Sultan Abdul Hamid II.
events.html: • 1909 – The 31 March Incident leads to the overthrow of Sultan Abdul Hamid II.

events.description: Jallianwala Bagh massacre: British Indian Army troops led by Brigadier-General Reginald Dyer kill approximately 379–1,000 unarmed demonstrators including men and women in Amritsar, India; and approximately 1,500 injured.
events.html: • 1919 – Jallianwala Bagh massacre: British Indian Army troops led by Brigadier-General Reginald Dyer kill approximately 379–1,000 unarmed demonstrators including men and women in Amritsar, India; and approximately 1,500 injured.[15]

events.description: A pact of neutrality between the USSR and Japan is signed.
events.html: • 1941 – A pact of neutrality between the USSR and Japan is signed.

events.description: World War II: The discovery of mass graves of Polish prisoners of war killed by Soviet forces in the Katyń Forest Massacre is announced, causing a diplomatic rift between the Polish government-in-exile in London and the Soviet Union, which denies responsibility.
events.html: • 1943 – World War II: The discovery of mass graves of Polish prisoners of war killed by Soviet forces in the Katyń Forest Massacre is announced, causing a diplomatic rift between the Polish government-in-exile in London and the Soviet Union, which denies responsibility.

events.description: The Jefferson Memorial is dedicated in Washington, D.C., on the 200th anniversary of President Thomas Jefferson's birth.
events.html: • 1943 – The Jefferson Memorial is dedicated in Washington, D.C., on the 200th anniversary of President Thomas Jefferson's birth.

events.description: World War II: German troops kill more than 1,000 political and military prisoners in Gardelegen, Germany.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: German troops kill more than 1,000 political and military prisoners in Gardelegen, Germany.

events.description: World War II: Soviet and Bulgarian forces capture Vienna.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Soviet and Bulgarian forces capture Vienna.

events.description: In an ambush, 78 Jewish doctors, nurses and medical students from Hadassah Hospital, and a British soldier, are massacred by Arabs in Sheikh Jarrah. This event came to be known as the Hadassah medical convoy massacre.
events.html: • 1948 – In an ambush, 78 Jewish doctors, nurses and medical students from Hadassah Hospital, and a British soldier, are massacred by Arabs in Sheikh Jarrah. This event came to be known as the Hadassah medical convoy massacre.

events.description: CIA director Allen Dulles launches the mind-control program Project MKUltra.
events.html: • 1953 – CIA director Allen Dulles launches the mind-control program Project MKUltra.

events.description: The United States launches Transit 1-B, the world's first satellite navigation system.
events.html: • 1960 – The United States launches Transit 1-B, the world's first satellite navigation system.

events.description: At the Academy Awards, Sidney Poitier becomes the first African-American man to win the Best Actor award for the 1963 film Lilies of the Field.
events.html: • 1964 – At the Academy Awards, Sidney Poitier becomes the first African-American man to win the Best Actor award for the 1963 film Lilies of the Field.

events.description: An oxygen tank aboard the Apollo 13 Service Module explodes, putting the crew in great danger and causing major damage to the Apollo command and service module (codenamed "Odyssey") while en route to the Moon.
events.html: • 1970 – An oxygen tank aboard the Apollo 13 Service Module explodes, putting the crew in great danger and causing major damage to the Apollo command and service module (codenamed "Odyssey") while en route to the Moon.

events.description: The Universal Postal Union decides to recognize the People's Republic of China as the only legitimate Chinese representative, effectively expelling the Republic of China administering Taiwan.
events.html: • 1972 – The Universal Postal Union decides to recognize the People's Republic of China as the only legitimate Chinese representative, effectively expelling the Republic of China administering Taiwan.

events.description: Vietnam War: The Battle of An Lộc begins.
events.html: • 1972 – Vietnam War: The Battle of An Lộc begins.

events.description: An attack by the Phalangist resistance kills 26 militia members of the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine, marking the start of the 15-year Lebanese Civil War.
events.html: • 1975 – An attack by the Phalangist resistance kills 26 militia members of the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine, marking the start of the 15-year Lebanese Civil War.

entities.name: Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine

events.description: The United States Treasury Department reintroduces the two-dollar bill as a Federal Reserve Note on Thomas Jefferson's 233rd birthday as part of the United States Bicentennial celebration.
events.html: • 1976 – The United States Treasury Department reintroduces the two-dollar bill as a Federal Reserve Note on Thomas Jefferson's 233rd birthday as part of the United States Bicentennial celebration.

events.description: Forty workers die in an explosion at the Lapua ammunition factory, the deadliest accidental disaster in modern history in Finland.
events.html: • 1976 – Forty workers die in an explosion at the Lapua ammunition factory, the deadliest accidental disaster in modern history in Finland.

events.description: Two women and four children are killed after Israeli helicopter fired rockets at an ambulance in Mansouri, Lebanon.
events.html: • 1996 – Two women and four children are killed after Israeli helicopter fired rockets at an ambulance in Mansouri, Lebanon.[16]

events.description: Tiger Woods becomes the youngest golfer to win the Masters Tournament.
events.html: • 1997 – Tiger Woods becomes the youngest golfer to win the Masters Tournament.

events.description: The house of Jack Teixeira is raided in an investigation into leaked Pentagon documents; he is arrested on the same day.
events.html: • 2023 – The house of Jack Teixeira is raided in an investigation into leaked Pentagon documents; he is arrested on the same day.[17][18]

events.description: Six people and the perpetrator are killed and twelve others injured in a mass stabbing at Westfield Bondi Junction shopping centre in Sydney, Australia.
events.html: • 2024 – Six people and the perpetrator are killed and twelve others injured in a mass stabbing at Westfield Bondi Junction shopping centre in Sydney, Australia.[19]
